who died.

23
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:40,290
Otherwise, China will look weak.

24
00:01:40,290 --> 00:01:46,710
In a pointless border clash where everyone
loses, it’s still important to win.

25
00:01:46,710 --> 00:01:52,909
China’s announcement came with a propaganda
video that shows brave Chinese soldiers at

26
00:01:52,909 --> 00:01:58,200
the border diplomatically diffusing tensions
with the Indian side.

27
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:02,420
And it eulogizes the four soldiers who were
said to have died.

28
00:02:02,420 --> 00:02:07,150
They died, by the way, not at the hands of
the Indian soldiers—no!

29
00:02:07,150 --> 00:02:11,880
They died trying to rescue their comrades.

30
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:18,670
But I have some bad news: Some Chinese netizens
saw this and began questioning whether what

31
00:02:18,670 --> 00:02:22,280
state-run media were reporting really adds
up.

32
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:26,230
The good news is: China already has a law
to handle that.

33
00:02:26,230 --> 00:02:32,530
